channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: BREAKING: Hezbollah #2 Leader Reportedly Taken Out in Airstrike
President Biden had front row seat to dog, Commander, repeatedly biting Secret Service agents: report
item.description: According to email correspondence, obtained by Judicial Watch, President Biden had a front row seat in witnessing his dog, Commander, attacking U.S. Secret Service agents on numerous occasions.

item.title: Rep. Burchett to Newsmax: Trump 'on Fire' in GOP Powwow
item.description: Rep. Tim Burchett, R-Tenn., set the record straight about Donald Trump's meeting with congressional Republicans on Thursday, telling Newsmax that the former president "was on fire" and on point.

item.title: Elon Musk Might Just Get a Little Richer As Board Reinstates $56 Billion Pay Package
Fettermanâ€™s driving record includes speeding, alleged texts and FaceTime calls: reports
item.description: Sen. Jon Fetterman, D-Pa., reportedly has a record of speeding, but also allegedly has been seen texting and using FaceTime while driving, according to reports.

item.title: Man Charged With Threatening FBI Agent After Hunter Verdict
item.description: A Texas man has been charged with allegedly threatening an FBI special agent who had been involved in an investigation into the dissemination of personal data from Hunter Biden's laptop, federal prosecutors said Thursday.

item.title: WHCA Throws Biden Under the Bus After He Snaps at Reporter, Claims He Has 'Deals' With the Press
James Carville sounds off on Dems hemorrhaging support of Latino male voters: 'We're gonna f---in lose 'em!'
item.description: Democratic strategist James Carville said that the Democratic Party is going to lose male voters, pointing to "preachy females" in the party.

item.title: Sen. Graham Slams Biden's Border Policies Amid ISIS Fears
item.description: Sen. Lindsey Graham, R-S.C., sharply criticized the Biden administration's border security policies Thursday in a news release following a recent report by the Inspector General of the Department of Homeland Security (DHS).

item.title: Trump Meets With 80 CEOs and Tells Them Exactly What He'll Do If Elected President Again
NASA administrator says 'at least a trillion' other planets like Earth could exist in universe
item.description: NASA Administrator Bill Nelson said the government agency aims to send astronauts back to the moon, while the Perseverance Rover explores what was once a lake on Mars.

item.title: Matthew Whitaker to Newsmax: Abortion Pill Decision Win for Rule of Law
item.description: Matthew Whitaker told Newsmax on Thursday the Supreme Court's unanimous ruling that preserved access to mifepristone, a medication that was used in nearly two-thirds of all abortions in the U.S. last year, was a victory for the rule of law.

item.title: 'Reporter' Gets Exactly the Reaction He Deserves After Term He Used to Describe Inverted US Flags
Trump endorses blue state Republican Senate candidate who does not support the former president
item.description: Former President Trump told Fox News he'd "like to see" anti-Trump Republican and former Gov. Larry Hogan flip a Democrat-held seat in the blue state of Maryland.

item.title: Rep. Steube to Newsmax: Congressional Ballgame 'Blessing'
item.description: Rep. Greg Steube, R-Fla., told Newsmax there was a lot to like from Wednesday night's annual congressional baseball game: Republicans routed the Democrats; the sides raised $2.2 million for charity; and watching protesters get tackled was pretty fun, too.
